column7: Well done summarizing your coding journey so far! Keep it up!
column8: Those are some great insights into your development. Well done!
column9: We're glad that you overcame the struggles you faced this week!
column10: Don't forget you can also reach out to a coach! Schedule a call with a coach at calendly.com/joyofcodinghlep/ask-a-coach
column11: Please answer the questions and resubmit.
column12: We'd love to read the answers to your reflection prompts. We get that this reflecting on a success *after* one has surmounted it can feel unnecessary.   Yet, this simple act of reflecting on how/why/what you did what you did to solve a problem has the magical effect of your brain operating at a higher level -- the act of reflecting literally strengthens the "learn to code" part of your brain ! So do share with us these answers now, or in future codices. It's never required - just, strongly encouraged because of all of the above :-)
